[{"kind":1,"language":"markdown","value":"# Model registration - SAS","outputs":[]},{"kind":1,"language":"markdown","value":"","outputs":[]},{"kind":2,"language":"sas","value":"libname mylib '/workspaces/myfolder/myscripts/data';\n\ndata mylib.hmeq;\n    set sampsio.hmeq;\nrun;\n\nproc treesplit data = mylib.hmeq;\n   input loan value mortdue debtinc derog / level = interval;\n   input job / level = nominal;\n   target bad / level = nominal;\n   prune none;\n   saveState rstore = mylib.treeStore_hmeq;\nrun;","outputs":[]},{"kind":1,"language":"markdown","value":"The PROC ASTORE Statement has been used to retrieve the external binary analytic store produced by the TREESPLIT procedure and stores it in the local file system. To do that, the following 2 options must be specified in the DOWNLOAD statement:\n- RSTORE. It specifies the data table that contains the state to be downloaded.\n- STORE. It specifies either the file reference or the full path of the local analytic store file to which the contents of the data table are to be downloaded.","outputs":[]},{"kind":2,"language":"sas","value":"proc astore;\n   download rstore = mylib.treeStore_hmeq\n            store = \"/workspaces/myfolder/myscripts/treeAstore.sasast\";\nrun;\n\n/* get token */\n%macro myTokenName() / secure;\n\"Bearer eyJqa3UiOiJodHRwczovL2xvY2FsaG9zdC9TQVNMb2dvbi90b2tlbl9rZXlzIiwia2lkIjoibGVnYWN5LXRva2VuLWtleSIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCIsImFsZyI6IlJTMjU2In0.\neyJzdWIiOiJkMTE0ODRiZC0xYTE0LTQyY2ItOGU3OS1mZjNiOGIxMDM4MzQiLCJ1c2VyX25hbWUiOiJNYXR0aWEuR3VnbGllbG1lbGxpQHNhcy5jb20iLCJvcmlnaW4iOiJh\nenVyZSIsImlzcyI6Imh0dHA6Ly9sb2NhbGhvc3QvU0FTTG9nb24vb2F1dGgvdG9rZW4iLCJhdXRob3JpdGllcyI6WyJTQVNTY29yZVVzZXJzIiwiRGF0YUJ1aWxkZXJzIiwi\nR2xvc3NhcnkuR2xvc3NhcnlBZG1pbmlzdHJhdG9ycyIsIkNJUyBWaXlhIEFsd2F5cyBPbiIsIkNhdGFsb2cuU3ViamVjdE1hdHRlckV4cGVydHMiLCJBcHBsaWNhdGlvbkFk\nbWluaXN0cmF0b3JzIiwiSUNVcyIsIk1pZ3JhdGlvbkFkbWlucyIsIkVzcmlVc2VycyIsIkNBU0hvc3RBY2NvdW50UmVxdWlyZWQiXSwiY2xpZW50X2lkIjoic2FzLmxhdW5j\naGVyIiwiYXVkIjpbInNhcy5sYXVuY2hlciIsInVhYSJdLCJleHRfaWQiOiI5Vjd0QTJpY01ubzc0WTQ4a1lNZDdRenJIbFRTaHdxeHF3eWpPLUtGdFpzIiwiemlkIjoidWFh\nIiwiZ3JhbnRfdHlwZSI6InVybjppZXRmOnBhcmFtczpvYXV0aDpncmFudC10eXBlOmp3dC1iZWFyZXIiLCJ1c2VyX2lkIjoiZDExNDg0YmQtMWExNC00MmNiLThlNzktZmYz\nYjhiMTAzODM0IiwiYXpwIjoic2FzLmxhdW5jaGVyIiwic2NvcGUiOlsidWFhLnVzZXIiXSwiZXhwIjoxNzI4MDMzNzU1LCJpYXQiOjE3MjgwMzAxNTUsImp0aSI6IjYyMGI3\nODVhZGQwODRlOGY4ODdjNGI2MjE0NDUxYTg3IiwiZW1haWwiOiJNYXR0aWEuR3VnbGllbG1lbGxpQHNhcy5jb20iLCJyZXZfc2lnIjoiNTY0MzY2YTkiLCJjaWQiOiJzYXMu\nbGF1bmNoZXIifQ.sZ9qK1KJDaM16-KMvS1R14EwRdRorDNQhVax0GK7-IWXXwF25M8hLSJhzl6FOiHIypwcnbf9LH_OqGCZEDcNakfFq6e0W5sjfS7KyppqVjBndOuv1YqOa\njhHrTe879hIHvIFJSK0dmkrSr5aIBGSmVxu1bPzkGMM0gdkY5VuT1zT_Qje9vk0ZFlXbt-hxqebAKgxyqjGZWOTAan7eDecqG7k10Z6aYj_UVqb-TLM_uoQ1NM3FE30LWnPk\nHwKMRQs8VPV8MfKWbh1tdT66f_Lw-_K2cELXnMcKJFE1OlRioVMAznUBY05M6pdQPvLTiOG7m_HD_LeH5G-mRw3lBUfrg\"\n%mend;","outputs":[]},{"kind":1,"language":"markdown","value":"We are now ready to use the REGISTERMODEL procedure to register the model in SAS Model Manager.\nPROC REGISTERMODEL Statement Options:\n- NAME (required). It specifies the name to register the model under in SAS Model Manager.\n- OAUTHTOKEN (required). It specifies the name of the authentication token for connecting to SAS Model Manager.\n- SERVER (required). It specifies the root URL for your SAS Viya server where SAS Model Manager is located.\n- ALGORITHM (optional). It specifies the algorithm that was used to train the model.\n- DATA (optional). It names the input data table for PROC REGISTERMODEL to use. The default is the most recently created data table.\n- DESCRIPTION (optional). It specifies the description of the model.\n- FUNCTION (optional). It specifies the model function type.\n- REPLACE (optional). It specifies that you want to replace an existing model with a new one if the new model would have the same model name in the same project.\n\nThe ASSESSMENT Statement enables you to assess the model and register assessment statistics in SAS Model Manager. To enable assessment:\n- the FUNCTION option value in the PROC REGISTERMODEL statement must be PREDICTION or CLASSIFICATION.\n- the TARGET statement must be specified.\n- the DATA option in the PROC REGISTERMODEL statement must be specified to provide the training data table.\n\nThe ASTOREMODEL Statement names an analytic store to be registered. You must specify the STORE option, which names the external file that contains the analytic store holding the model to be registered.\n\nThe PROJECT Statement specifies the project in which to register the model. In our case, we specify the name of the SAS Model Manager project to register the model in, and the folder name where the SAS Model Manager project resides.\n\nThe TARGET Statement names the variable whose values the model tries to predict. The following two options must be specified after typing the variable name:\n- LEVEL. It specifies the level of measurement of the target variable. In our case, the measurement level is binary.\n- EVENT. It must be specified if LEVEL=BINARY or NOMINAL. In these cases, it specifies the event level of the target.\n\nTo avoid SSL certificate issues, set the `SSLREQCERT=\"allow\"`, which allows to run PROC REGISTERMODEL even if no certificate is provided:","outputs":[]},{"kind":2,"language":"sas","value":"options set=SSLREQCERT=\"allow\";\n\nproc registermodel\n      name = \"Tree Astore\"\n      description = \"Decision Tree Astore Model\"\n      data = mylib.hmeq\n      algorithm = TREE\n      function = CLASSIFICATION\n      server = \"https://create.demo.sas.com\"\n      oauthtoken = \"myTokenName\"\n      replace;\n   project name=\"registermodel-project\" folder=\"myFolder\";\n   astoremodel store = \"treeAstore.sasast\";\n   target bad / level=binary event=\"1\";\n   assessment;\nrun;","outputs":[]},{"kind":1,"language":"markdown","value":"**Note**. In order to connect to SAS Model Manager, your SAS Viya server where SAS Model Manager is located must have the IP address of your SAS Viya Workbench in its allowed IP ranges. If you need to change the allowed IP ranges, please contact your SAS administrator.","outputs":[]},{"kind":1,"language":"markdown","value":"","outputs":[]}]